snippet.textDisplay: Voices of rural Gujarat and its folklore! Wow! I have a distinct memory as a kid to listen to faint echoes of Garbis reverberating in the distance in the quite of the night coming from village outskirts. It was mystical yet ill-understood to me back then, may be because i grew up in a village where inter-faith peace was always there however very little exchange of knowledge about each other's customs, thoughts and folklore music. I used to wonder what were they singing so late in the night? celebration of some sort? appeasing local deity for a good harvest or for signs of monsoon?? Would never know. Regret not knowing more of the culture, religion and customs of Gujarati Hinduism. Little off topic here but just thought it would be good idea to share. Great composition by all artists especially Kirtidan.
